{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea96661c-5d62-4b74-b0f6-7a6f3b5a38a5","content":"The project is small — just one file. Here's the scan result:\n\n### Static Dependency Report\n\n| File | Line | Call | Risk |\n|------|------|------|------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` | 🔴 High — non-deterministic, untestable |\n\n**1 static call site found.**\n\n#### Why it's a problem\n`datetime.now()` is hardcoded, so tests can't control the returned time. Assertions on the rendered `time` value become flaky or impossible.\n\n#### Recommended fix (Django-idiomatic)\nUse Django's `django.utils.timezone.now` and mock it with [`freezegun`](https://github.com/spulec/freezegun) or `unittest.mock.patch` in tests:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nThen in tests:\n```python\nfrom freezegun import freeze_time\n\n@freeze_time(\"2026-01-01\")\ndef test_index(self):\n    ...\n```\n\nWant me to apply this fix?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ea5d770d-8e30-4035-b9d7-c53ac82c0da6","outputTokens":286,"requestId":"5C24:2DE364:226735C:276293A:69F561DF"},"id":"e9d05f2b-5e3c-4645-9203-6a0f8e1398c8","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:31:03.017Z","parentId":"941cc774-cd43-40a3-b4c9-5e7cb0ce2e92"}
